<div id="review_332252514" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/332252514" />
    <a title="Pallak" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6267483-pallak"><img alt="Pallak" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1459605078p2/6267483.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/332252514?book_show_action=true">May 18, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Pallak" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Pallak" href="/user/show/6267483-pallak">Pallak</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer332252514" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17865284922163289029">Animal&apos;s People is an insight into the lives of people of contemporary India. It&apos;s about a boy who is on his all fours ever since the Bhopal disaster took place in India and devastated the lives of thousands of innocent people. Even after several years, babies are still born with various disorders. The story is about the fight between the American owners of the company and the innocent people who are still facing the after-effects of the disaster. <br/>This book is a good read as it gives a glimpse o</span>
  <span id="freeText17865284922163289029" style="display:none">Animal's People is an insight into the lives of people of contemporary India. It's about a boy who is on his all fours ever since the Bhopal disaster took place in India and devastated the lives of thousands of innocent people. Even after several years, babies are still born with various disorders. The story is about the fight between the American owners of the company and the innocent people who are still facing the after-effects of the disaster. <br />This book is a good read as it gives a glimpse of how the people of Bhopal are still facing various problems, their behavior towards the Americans, how they feel that every American is guilty (though not true), and why they don't want to trust any American again. <br />I think this book can be better understood by those whose mother tongue is "Hindi" or who can understand "Hindi" very well. It contains many sentences in Hindi/Urdu, so it might get a little irritating for those who can't understand either of them. <br />But in all, it's a nice read. Very straight-forward story. It's a Booker nominee and I feel it deserves to be so. I give it 4 stars. :)</span>
  <a data-text-id="17865284922163289029" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


