<div id="review_353182577" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/353182577" />
    <a title="Chaitra" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9086236-chaitra"><img alt="Chaitra" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1432611617p2/9086236.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/353182577?book_show_action=true">Jun 21, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Chaitra" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Chaitra" href="/user/show/9086236-chaitra">Chaitra</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9781416578789" href="/book/show/2430071.Animal_s_People">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9086236-chaitra?shelf=romance">romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9086236-chaitra?shelf=literary-fiction">literary-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9086236-chaitra?shelf=contemporary-fiction">contemporary-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9086236-chaitra?shelf=disaster">disaster</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9086236-chaitra?shelf=indian-literature">indian-literature</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9086236-chaitra?shelf=child-or-teenage-protagonist">child-or-teenage-protagonist</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9086236-chaitra?shelf=booker-prize-nominees">booker-prize-nominees</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9086236-chaitra?shelf=1001-books">1001-books</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer353182577" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15449741478312982362">The book has a great premise - I grew up with stories about the Bhopal Gas tragedy (my family was too far away to be harmed). Animal has a very funny, distinctive voice. The characters are well drawn, and I could see them before my Eyes. I even liked the fact that it sounded exactly as it was described - like it was translated from Animal&apos;s version of Hindi, with no attention paid to grammar. That&apos;s why I&apos;ve given the three stars. But I could not relate to Animal - at all. <br/><br/>I guess the repeated-i</span>
  <span id="freeText15449741478312982362" style="display:none">The book has a great premise - I grew up with stories about the Bhopal Gas tragedy (my family was too far away to be harmed). Animal has a very funny, distinctive voice. The characters are well drawn, and I could see them before my Eyes. I even liked the fact that it sounded exactly as it was described - like it was translated from Animal's version of Hindi, with no attention paid to grammar. That's why I've given the three stars. But I could not relate to Animal - at all. <br /><br />I guess the repeated-in-every-page assertion that he's an animal put me off. Sometimes he says he's been given that name by others but most of the times it serves as an excuse to do exactly the opposite his conscience suggests. Other characters call him out on it, but they remain stubbornly fond of him. No one ever, not even Farouq - his supposed sworn enemy - falls out with him in any sort of permanent fashion. Zafar gets poisoned by him, Nisha propositioned against her will, Elli spied on, Somraj blabbered against, but no one ever seriously thinks ill of Animal. I guess I did not think Animal charming enough to swallow this unreasonable love of him by everyone.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15449741478312982362" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


